<main class="col">
  <h2>A partnership graph measures strategy</h2>
  <p class="pull">Anthropic&rsquo;s position on this map is not luck. It is the network signature of a specific bet: power other companies&rsquo; agents rather than compete with them.</p>
  <p>Anthropic sells picks and shovels to the agent economy and publishes the customer story; every case study becomes an edge. OpenAI&rsquo;s empire runs through channels that don&rsquo;t create partnership edges at all &mdash; 900 million weekly ChatGPT users, Stargate-scale compute, classified government networks. Two companies of comparable size produce completely different network signatures because they are playing different games: Anthropic is becoming infrastructure, OpenAI is becoming a destination.</p>
  <p>The market data agrees with the graph. Menlo Ventures&rsquo; enterprise survey has Anthropic at 40% of enterprise LLM API spend to OpenAI&rsquo;s 27%, and 54% to 21% in coding &mdash; and the gap widened all year. Anthropic&rsquo;s revenue run-rate crossed OpenAI&rsquo;s around March 2026 ($47B against roughly $25B at OpenAI&rsquo;s S-1). Its Series H priced it at $965B, above OpenAI&rsquo;s $852B. MCP, the protocol Anthropic wrote, became the standard plumbing of the agent ecosystem &mdash; roughly 97 million SDK downloads a month before it was donated to the Linux Foundation.</p>

  <h2>The scoreboard, honestly kept</h2>
